<h2>Templates and sending</h2>
<h3>One Logo, many templates.</h3>
<p>A cool new feature in phpList 3.2.2 allows the upload of a logo to the main settings page. The logo can then be inserted into campaign templates using the new [LOGO] placeholder: this system helps you change the logo across all templates in one go, with just a few clicks. <a href="https://www.phplist.org/phplist-3-2-2-one-logo-many-templates">Read this blog to find out how to use it</a>.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/campaign-example.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2626" src="https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/campaign-example.png" alt="campaign-example" width="480" height="487" srcset="https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/campaign-example.png 860w, https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/campaign-example-286x290.png 286w, https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/campaign-example-443x450.png 443w" sizes="(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px" /></a></p>
<h3>Send-a-webpage failsafe</h3>
<p>phpList will now check that the url of the webpage you want to send exists before you queue, broken urls will bring up an error. Additionally, if you click. Send-a-webpage and want to change back, you can now do so.</p>
<p><a href="https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/send-a-webpage-2.png"><img class="alignnone wp-image-2640" src="https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/send-a-webpage-2.png" alt="send-a-webpage-2" width="480" height="130" srcset="https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/send-a-webpage-2.png 711w, https://www.phplist.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/11/send-a-webpage-2-290x78.png 290w" sizes="(max-width: 480px) 100vw, 480px" /></a></p>
<h3>Small fix</h3>
<p>Placeholders such as [PREFERENCESURL] will now be accepted under the “Check that URLs are valid&#8221; checkbox test.</p>
<h2>Statistics</h2>
<h3>Response time fix and clarification</h3>
<p>The “response time” number in a subscribers history tells you the length of time between when you sent a campaign and when the subscriber opened it. If the subscriber opens the campaign a few times, this will now show the first time of opening only. Thanks to lwc for his question.</p>
<h2>Subscriber and user management</h2>
<h3>Only ever one un-subscribe confirm message</h3>
<p>The un-subscribe confirm message should now only be sent one time, even if the subscriber leave the page open or keeps refreshing it.</p>
<h3>Sub-admin password reset bug fixed</h3>
<p>If a non-super-admin account did not have the permission to &#8220;change settings&#8221;, password reset would fail. Thanks to sd3pk3 for reporting this issue, and for confirming the fix in 3.2.1 and 2.</p>
<h2>Submit by mail plugin update</h2>
<p>There has been an important update to the Submit-by-mail plugin, by <a href="http://phplist.org/our-team/arnoldvl/profile/">Arnoldvl</a>, to make it compatible with phpList 3.2.*. <a href="https://discuss.phplist.org/t/submit-by-mail-plugin-updated-for-phplist-3-2/1074">Click here for more information</a>.</p>
